== English ==
=== Etymology ===
'''aleck''' is a [[nickname]] for [[Alexander]].  The phrase is possibly derived from the name Aleck Hoag, a 19<sup>th</sup> century [[con man]] and thief.

=== Noun ===
'''smart aleck''' ''or'' '''smart alec'''
# one who is [[pretentious]] to [[cleverness]] or [[knowledge]]
# one who is [[obnoxiously]] self assured

